- "Treasure they've amassed" refers to the total revenue generated by the team;
- "Victorious series" refers to the championship series where the team was the champion.

- `COUNT(team_id)` calculates the number of teams with the same `team_name`;
- `AVG(LENGTH(team_name))` calculates the average length of the team names;
- `MAX(LENGTH(team_name))` finds the maximum length of the team names.

- "championship series" refers to a series of games played to determine the champion;
- "average attendance" is the mean number of spectators per game in a series;
- "average revenue" is the mean financial income per game in a series;
- "average points scored by players" is the mean points scored per player across all games in the series.

sql:
SELECT total_attendance, total_revenue, series_score, schedule_length
FROM championship_series
WHERE total_attendance > 100000;

